obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (722)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=722&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1****;`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 25 of 1968, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
  line
  line `2. 28th May, 1959, vide notification No. G.S.R. 610, dated 25th May, 1959, see Gazette of India, Extraordinry, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (723)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Definitions and interpretation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=723&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "associate" means an associate member of the Institute;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) "Authority" means the Appellate Authority referred to in section 22A;`
  line
  line `(aaa) "Board" means the Quality Review Board constituted under section 29A];`
  line
  line `^2[(ab) Board of Discipline" means the Board of Discipline constituted under sub-section (1) of section 21A;`
  line
  line `(ac) "Companies Act" means the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) or any other previous company law as defined in clause (67) of section 2 of the said Act;]`
  line
  line `(b) cost accountant means a person who is a member of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) Council means the Council of the Institute ^2[constituted under section 9];`
  line
  line `^2[(ca) "Director (Discipline)" means the Director (Discipline) referred to in section 21 and includes Joint Director (Discipline);`
  line
  line `(cb)"Disciplinary Committee"means the Disciplinary Committee constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 21B;`
  line
  line `(cc) "Disciplinary Directorate" means the Disciplinary Directorate established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 21;]`
  line
  line `(d) "dissolved" company means the Institute of Cost and Works Accountants registered under the Companies Act, ^3****;`
  line
  line `^4[(e) "fellow" means a fellow member of the Institute];`
  line
  line `^5[(ea) "firm" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4 of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), and includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) the limited liability partnership as defined in clause (n) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of`
  line `the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009); or`
  line
  line `(ii) the sole proprietorship,`
  line
  line `registered with the Institute;]`
  line
  line `(f) "Institute" means the ^6[Institute of Cost Accountants of India] constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `^7[(fa) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the term notify shall be construed accordingly;]`
  line
  line `^8[(fb) partner shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4 of the Indian Partnership Act,1932 (9 of 1932) or in clause (q) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009), as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(fc) "partnership" means--`
  line
  line `(A) a partnership as defined in section 4 of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932); or`
  line
  line `(B) a limited liability partnership which has no company as its Partner;]`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "President" means the President of the Council;`
  line
  line `^9[(i) "Register" means the Register of members of the Institute maintained under section 19 or`
  line `Register of firms of the Institute maintained under section 20B, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line ;
  line
  line `^10[(ia) "specified" means specified by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `^8[(iaa) sole proprietorship means an individual who engages himself in the practice of cost accountancy or offers to perform services referred to in clauses (ii) to (iv) of sub-section (2);]`
  line
  line `^2[(iaaa) "Standing Committee" means a Standing Committee constituted under sub-section (1) of section 17;]`
  line
  line `(ib) "Tribunal" means a Tribunal established under sub-section (1) of section 10B;]`
  line
  line `(j) "Vice-President" means the Vice-President of the Council;`
  line
  line `(k) "year" means the period commencing on the 1st day of April of any year and ending on the 31st day of March of the succeeding year.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, a member of the Institute shall be deemed to be in practice when, individually or in partnership with one or more members of the Institute in practice, ^8[or in partnership with members of such other recognised professions as may be prescribed] he, in consideration of remuneration received or to be received,--`
  line
  line `(i) engages himself in the practice of ^11[cost accountancy]; or`
  line
  line `(ii) offers to perform or performs services involving the costing or pricing of goods or services or the preparation, verification or ^12[certification or auditing of cost accounting and related statements or holds himself out to the public as a cost accountant in practice]; or`
  line
  line `(iii) renders professional services or assistance in or about matters of principle or detail relating to cost accounting procedure or the recording, presentation or certification of costing facts or data; or`
  line
  line `(iv) renders such other services as, in the opinion of the Council, are or may be rendered by a cost accountant in practice;`
  line
  line `and the words to be in practice, with their grammatical variations and cognate expressions, shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A member of the Institute who is a whole-time salaried employee of any person shall not be deemed to be in practice within the meaning of this sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 40 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. The figure "1956" omitted by s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for clause (e) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2012, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Institute of Cost and Works Accountants of India" (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 40, for clause (fa) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 10 of 2012, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 40, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for cost and works accountancy (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for certification of cost accounting and related statements or holds himself out to the public as a cost accountant in practice (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (724)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Incorporation of the Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for Institute of Cost and Works Accountants of India (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=724&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) All persons whose names are entered in the Register at the`
  line `commencement of this Act and all persons who may hereafter have their names entered in the Register under the provisions of this Act, so long as they continue to have their names borne on the said Register, are hereby constituted a body corporate by the name of the ^1[Institute of Cost Accountants of India], and all such persons shall be known as members of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Institute shall have perpetual succession and a common seal, and shall have power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and shall by its name sue or be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (725)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Entry of names in the Register of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=725&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any of the following persons shall be entitled to have his name entered in the ^1[Register of members], namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) any person who was an associate or a fellow of the dissolved company (other than an honorary associate or honorary fellow thereof) immediately before the commencement of this Act, except any such person who is not a permanent resident of India and is not at such commencement practicing as a cost accountant in India;`
  line
  line `(ii) any person who has passed such examination and completed such training as may be prescribed for members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(iii) any person who, at the commencement of this Act, is engaged in the practice of cost accountancy in India and who fulfills such conditions as the Central Government or the Council may specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(iv) any person who has passed such other examination and completed such other training ^2[outside India] as is recognised by the Central Government or the Council as being equivalent to the examination and training prescribed for members of the Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any person who is not permanently residing in India, the Central Government or the Council may impose such further conditions as it may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(v) any person domiciled in India, who at the commencement of this Act is studying for any foreign examination and is at the same time undergoing training, whether within or ^2[outside India], or, who, having passed such examination, is at such commencement undergoing training whether within or ^2[outside India]:`
  line
  line `Provided that such foreign examination and training are recognised by the Central Government or the Council in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the person passes the examination and completes his training within five years from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person belonging to the class mentioned in clause (i) of sub-section (1) shall have his name entered in the ^1[Register of members] without the payment of any entrance fee.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every person belonging to any of the classes mentioned in clauses (ii), (iii), (iv) and (v) of sub-section (1) shall have his name entered in the ^1[Register of members] on an application being made and granted in the prescribed manner and on payment of such fees, as may be determined, by notification, by the Council ^4***:`
  line
  line ^5*****]
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall take such steps as may be necessary for the purpose of having the names of all persons belonging to the class mentioned in clause (i) of sub-section (1) entered in the ^1[Register of members] at the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 42, for “Register” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 42, ibid., for “without India” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 3, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `4. The words “, which shall not exceed rupees three thousand” omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 42 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. The proviso omitted by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (726)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Fellows and Associates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=726&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The members of the Institute shall be divided into two classes designated respectively as associates and fellows.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person other than a person to whom the provisions of sub-section (3) apply shall, on his name being entered in the ^1[Register of members], be deemed to have become an associate member of the Institute and so long as his name remains so entered, shall be entitled to use the letters ^2[ACMA] after his name to indicate that he is an associate member of the ^3[Institute of Cost Accountants of India].`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who was a fellow of the dissolved company and who is entitled to have his name entered in the ^1[Register of members] under clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 4, shall be entered in the ^1[Register of members]as a fellow of the Institute.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) A member, being an associate who has been in continuous practice in India for at least five years, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, or whether partly before and partly after the commencement of this Act, and a member who has been an associate for a continuous period of not less than five years and who possesses such qualifications as the Council may prescribe with a view to ensuring that he has experience equivalent to the experience normally acquired as a result of continuous practice for a period of five years as a cost accountant shall, on payment of such fees, as may be determined, by notification, by the Council, ^5***, and on application made and granted in the prescribed manner, be entered in the Register as a fellow of the Institute`
  line
  line ^6*****.
  line
  line `Explanation I.--For the purposes of this sub-section, a person shall be deemed to have practiced in India for any period for which he has held a certificate of practice under section 6, notwithstanding that he did not actually practice during that period.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--In computing the continuous period during which a person has been an associate of the Institute, there shall be included any continuous period during which the person has been an associate of the dissolved company immediately before he became an associate of the Institute.]`
  line
  line `(5) Any person whose name is entered in the^1[Register of members] as a fellow of the Institute and so long as his name remains so entered, shall be entitled to use the letters ^7[FCMA] after his name to indicate that he is a fellow of the ^3[Institute of Cost Accountants of India].`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 43, for "Register" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2012, s. 4, for "AICWA" (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, for "Institute of Cost and Works Accountants" (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 4, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `5. The words "which shall not exceed rupees five thousand," omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 43 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6. The proviso omitted by s. 43, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 10 of 2012, s. 4, for "FICWA" (w.e.f.1-2-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (727)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Certificate of practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=727&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) No member of the Institute shall be entitled to practise, whether in India or elsewhere, unless he has obtained from the Council a certificate of practice.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Every such member shall make an application in such form, and pay such annual fee, for his certificate as may be determined, by notification, by the Council, ^2*** and such fee shall be payable on or before the 1st day of April in each year:`
  line
  line `^3*****:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that] if a member of the Institute, who was in practice immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, has made within one month of such commencement an application for the grant of certificate of practice, he shall not be deemed to have contravened the provisions of sub-section (1) by reason of his having practiced during the period between such commencement and the disposal of the application;]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) The certificate of practice obtained under sub-section (1) may be cancelled by the Council under such circumstances as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 5, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `2. The words “which shall not exceed rupees three thousand” omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 44 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3.The proviso omitted by s. 44, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for “Provided further that” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (728)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Members to be known as cost accountants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=728&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Institute in practice shall, and any other member may, use the designation of a cost accountant and no member using such designation shall use any other description, whether in addition thereto or in substitution therefore:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prohibit any such member from adding any other description or letters to his name, if entitled thereto, to indicate membership of such other Institute of accountancy, whether in India or elsewhere, as may be recognised in this behalf by the Council, or any other qualification that he may possess, or to prohibit a firm, all the partners of which are members of the Institute and in practice, from being known by its firm name as cost accountants.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (729)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Disabilities.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=729&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 4, a person shall not be entitled to`
  line `have his name entered in, or borne on, the ^1[Register of members] if he--`
  line
  line `(i) has not attained the age of twenty-one years at the time of his application for the entry of his name in the ^1[Register of members]; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is of unsound mind and stands so adjudged by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(iii) is an undischarged insolvent ^2[or undischarged bankrupt]; or`
  line
  line `^2[(iiia) is declared bankrupt under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016);]`
  line
  line `(iv) being a discharged insolvent, has not obtained from the court a certificate stating that his insolvency was caused by misfortune without any misconduct on his part; or`
  line
  line `(v) has been convicted by a competent court whether within or ^3[outside India], of an offence`
  line `involving moral turpitude and punishable with imprisonment or of an offence, not of a technical nature, committed by him in his professional capacity unless in respect of the offence committed he has either been granted a pardon or, on an application made by him in this behalf, the Central Government has, by an order in writing removed the disability; or`
  line
  line `(vi) has been removed from membership of the Institute on being found on inquiry to have been guilty of professional or other misconduct:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has been removed from membership for a specified period, shall not be entitled to have his name entered in the ^1[Register of members] until the expiry of such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 45, for "Register" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 45, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for "without India" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (730)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Constitution of the Council of the Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=730&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Council of the Institute for the`
  line `management of the affairs of the Institute and for discharging the functions assigned to it by or under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `^1[(2) The Council shall be composed of the following persons, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) not more than fifteen persons elected by the members of the Institute, from amongst the`
  line `fellows of the Institute chosen in such manner and from such regional constituencies as may be`
  line `specified:`
  line
  line `Provided that a fellow of the Institute, who has been found guilty of any professional or other`
  line `misconduct, and whose name is removed from the ^2[Register of members] or has been awarded`
  line `penalty of fine, shall not be eligible to contest the election,—`
  line
  line `(i) in case of misconduct falling under the First Schedule of this Act, for a period of`
  line `^3[four years];`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of misconduct falling under the Second Schedule of this Act, for a period of`
  line `^4[eight years],`
  line `from the completion of the period of removal of name from the ^2[Register of members] or payment of`
  line `fine, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) not more than five persons nominated in the specified manner by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) No person holding a post under the Central Government or a State Government shall be eligible`
  line `for election to the Council under clause (a) of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) No ^6[member of the Institute or any partner of a firm] who has been auditor of the Institute shall`
  line `be eligible for election to the Council under clause (a) of sub-section (2) for a period of ^7`
  line `[four years] after`
  line `he ceases to be an auditor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 6, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 46, for "Register" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for "three years" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for "six years" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 46, for "person" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `7.Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for "three years" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (731)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Re-election or re-nomination to Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for section 10 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=731&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Re-election or re-nomination to Council.--A member of the Council, elected or nominated under sub-section (2) of section 9, shall be eligible for re-election or as the case may be, re-nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that no member shall hold the office for more than two consecutive terms:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a member of the Council, who is or has been elected as President under sub-section (1) of section 12, shall not be eligible for election or nomination as a member of the Council.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (732)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Settlement of disputes regarding election.`
  content `^1[10A. Settlement of disputes regarding election.--In case of any dispute regarding any election under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 9, the aggrieved person may make an application within thirty days from the date of declaration of the result of election to the Secretary of the Institute, who shall forward the same to the Central Government.]`
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 8 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=732&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_10_b:
  sectionId (733)
  sectionNo 10B
  orderNo 12
  title `Establishment of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 8 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=733&sectionno=10B&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[10B. Establishment of Tribunal.(1) On receipt of any application under section 10A, the Central Government shall, by notification, establish a Tribunal consisting of a Presiding Officer and two other`
  line `Members to decide such dispute and the decision of such Tribunal shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment,--`
  line
  line `(a) as a Presiding Officer of the Tribunal unless he has been a member of the Indian Legal`
  line `Service and has held a post in Grade I of the service for at least three years;`
  line
  line `(b) as a Member unless he has been a member of the Council for at least one full term, and who is not a sitting member of the Council or who has not been a candidate in the election under dispute; or`
  line
  line `(c) as a Member unless he holds the post of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India or any other post under the Central Government carrying a scale of pay which is not less than that of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions of service of the Presiding Officer and Members of the Tribunal, their place of meetings and allowances shall be such as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) The expenses of the Tribunal shall be borne by the Council.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (734)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Nomination in default of election.`
  content `If the members of the Institute fail to elect any member under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 9 from any of the regional constituencies that may be specified under that clause, the Central Government may nominate any duly qualified person from such constituency to fill the vacancy, and any person so nominated shall be deemed to be a duly elected member of the Council.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=734&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (735)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `President and Vice-president.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=735&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council at its first meeting shall elect two of its members to be respectively the President and the Vice-President thereof, and so often as the office of the President or the Vice-President becomes vacant, the Council shall choose a person to be the President or`
  line `the Vice-President, as the case may be:`
  line
  line ^1*****.
  line
  line `(2) The President shall be the ^2[Head] of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The President or the Vice-President shall hold office for a period of one year from the date on which he is chosen but so as not to extend beyond his term of office as a member of the Council, and, subject to his being a member of the Council at the relevant time, he shall be eligible for re-election ^3[under sub-section (1)]:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^4[the President and the Vice-President] of the Council at the time of the expiration of its duration shall continue to hold office until a new Council is constituted in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 47 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "Chief Executive Authority" (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "the President" (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (736)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Resignation of membership and casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=736&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any member of the Council may at any time resign his membership by writing under his hand addressed to the President, and the seat of such member shall become vacant when such resignation is notified in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) A member of the Council shall be deemed to have vacated his seat if he is declared by the Council to have been absent without sufficient excuse from three consecutive meetings of the Council ^1[or he has been found guilty of any professional or other misconduct and awarded penalty of fine], or if his name is, for any cause, removed from the ^2[Register of members] under the provisions of section 20.`
  line
  line `(3) A casual vacancy in the Council shall be filled by fresh election from the constituency concerned or by nomination by the Central Government, as the case may be, and the person elected or nominated to fill the vacancy shall hold office until the dissolution of the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that no election shall be held to fill a casual vacancy occurring within ^3[one year] prior to the date of the expiration of the duration of the Council, but such a vacancy may be filled by the nomination by the Central Government after consultation with the President of the Council.`
  line
  line `(4) No act done by the Council shall be called in question on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 10, (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 48, for “Register” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for six months (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (737)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Duration and dissolution of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for three years (w.e.f. 22-7-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=737&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The duration of any Council constituted under this Act shall be`
  line `^1[four years] from the date of its first meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the expiration of the duration of a Council (hereinafter referred to as the former Council), the former Council shall continue to exercise its functions under this Act until a new Council is constituted in accordance with the provisions of this Act, and on such constitution, the former Council shall stand dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (738)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Functions of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=738&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Functions of Council.--(1) The Institute shall function under the overall control, guidance and supervision of the Council and the duty of carrying out the provisions of this Act shall be vested in the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, the duties of the Council shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) to approve academic courses and their contents;`
  line
  line `(b) the prescribing of fees for the examination of candidates for enrolment;`
  line
  line `(c) the prescribing of qualifications for entry in the ^2[Register of members];`
  line
  line `(d) the recognition of foreign qualifications and training for the purposes of enrolment;`
  line
  line `(e) the prescribing of guidelines for granting or refusal of certificates of practice under this Act;`
  line
  line `^3[(ea) the granting or refusal, of registration of a firm;]`
  line
  line `(f) the levy of fees from members, examinees and other persons;`
  line
  line ^;
  line
  line `(h) the carrying out, by granting financial assistance to persons other than members of the`
  line `Council or in any other manner, of research in accountancy;`
  line
  line `(i) to enable functioning of the Director (Discipline), the Board of Discipline, the Disciplinary Committee and the Appellate Authority constituted under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) to enable functioning of the Quality Review Board;`
  line
  line `^3[(ja) to issue guidelines for the purpose of carrying out the objects of this Act;`
  line
  line `(jb) to conduct investor education and awareness programmes;`
  line
  line `(jc) to enter into any memorandum or arrangement with the prior approval of the Central`
  line `Government, with any agency of any foreign country, for the purpose of performing its functions`
  line `under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(k) consideration of the recommendations of the Quality Review Board made under clause (a) of section 29B ^4[and the details of action taken thereon in its annual report]; and`
  line
  line `(l) to ensure the functioning of the Institute in accordance with the provisions of this Act and in performance of other statutory duties as may be entrusted to the Institute from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 15 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 49, for "Register" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 49, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 49, ibid., for ", action taken thereon with a report to the Central Government within a period of three months, and their inclusion in the annual report" (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (739)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 18
  title `Functions of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=739&sectionno=15A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Functions of Institute.--The functions of the Institute shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) the examination of candidates for enrolment;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation of training of students;`
  line
  line `(c) the maintenance and publication of a Register of persons qualified to practice as cost`
  line accountants;
  line
  line `^2[(ca) the maintenance and publication of a Register of firms;]`
  line
  line `(d) collection of fees from members, examinees and other persons;`
  line
  line `(e) subject to the orders of the appropriate authorities under this Act, the removal of names from the ^3[Register of members and firms and the restoration of names to the Register of members and`
  line `firms] which have been removed;`
  line
  line `(f) the maintenance of a library and publication of books and periodicals relating to accountancy and allied subjects;`
  line
  line `(g) the conduct of elections to the Council of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(h) the granting or refusal of certificates of practice as per guidelines issued by the Council.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 13 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 50 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for “Register and the restoration to the Register of names” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (740)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 19
  title `Imparting education by Universities and other bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 13 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=740&sectionno=15B&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[15B. Imparting education by Universities and other bodies.--(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, any University established by law or any body affiliated to the Institute, may impart education on the subjects covered by the academic courses of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Universities or bodies referred to in sub-section (1) shall, while awarding degree, diploma or certificate or bestowing any designation, ensure that the award or designation do not resemble or is not identical to one awarded by the Institute.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall enable a University or a body to adopt a name or`
  line `nomenclature which is in any way similar to that of the Institute.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (741)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `Officers and employees, salary, allowances, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=741&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Officers and employees, salary, allowances, etc.--(1) For the efficient performance of its duties, the Council shall--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint a Secretary of the Council to perform such duties as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) appoint a Director (Discipline) to perform such functions as assigned to him under this Act and the rules and regulations framed thereunder;`
  line
  line `(c) designate an officer of the Council or the Institute to carry out the administrative functions of the Institute as its chief executive.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may also--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint such other officers and employees to the Council and the Institute as it considers necessary;`
  line
  line `(b) require and take from the Secretary or from any other officer or employee of the Council and the Institute such security for the due performance of his duties, as the Council considers necessary;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) prescribe the manner of appointment, powers, duties and functions of the Secretary and other`
  line `officers and employees, their salaries, fees, allowances and other terms and conditions of service];`
  line
  line `(d) with the previous sanction of the Central Government, fix the allowances of the President,`
  line `Vice-President and other members of the Council and members of its Committees.`
  line
  line `(3) The Secretary of the Council shall be entitled to participate in the meetings of the Council but shall not be entitled to vote thereat.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for section 16 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 51clause (ii), for clause (c) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (742)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Committees of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=742&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall constitute from amongst its members of the following Standing Committees, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) an Executive Committee;`
  line
  line `^1[(ii) a Finance Committee; and;]`
  line
  line `(iii) an Examination Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may also form a Training and Educational Facilities Committee and such other Committees from amongst its members as it deems necessary for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Each of the Standing Committees shall consist of the President and the Vice-President ex officio, and minimum of three and maximum of five members to be elected by the Council from amongst its members];`
  line
  line ^3*****
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, any Committee formed under sub-section (2), may, with the sanction of the Council, co-opt such other members of the Institute not exceeding ^4[one-third of total membership of the Committee] as the Committee thinks fit, and any member so co-opted shall be entitled to exercise all the rights of a member of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(7) The President shall be the Chairman of every Committee of which he is a member, arid in his absence, the Vice-President, if he is a member of the Committee, shall be the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(8) The Standing Committees and other Committees formed under this section shall exercise such functions and be subject to such conditions in the exercise thereof as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 15, for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-sections (4) and (5) omitted by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for two-thirds of total membership of the Committee (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (743)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Finances of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=743&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be established a fund under the management and control of the Council into which shall be paid all moneys received by the Council and out of which shall be met all expenses and liabilities properly incurred by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may invest any money for the time being standing to the credit of the fund in any Government security or in any other security approved by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The Council shall keep proper accounts of the fund distinguishing capital from revenue in the manner prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall prepare in the manner prescribed and approve, prior to the start of the financial year, an annual financial statement (the budget) indicating all its anticipated revenues as well as all proposed expenditures for the forthcoming year.`
  line
  line `^2[ (5) The annual accounts of the Council shall be prepared in such manner as may be prescribed and`
  line `subject to audit by a firm of chartered accountants to be appointed annually by the Council from the panel`
  line `of auditors maintained by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that a firm shall not be eligible for appointment as an auditor under this sub-section, if any`
  line `of its partner is or has been a member of the Council during the last four years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the event it is brought to the notice of the Council that the accounts of the`
  line `Council do not represent a true and fair view of its finances, then, the Council may itself cause a special`
  line `audit to be conducted:`
  line
  line `Provided also that, if such information, that the accounts of the Council do not represent a true and`
  line `fair view of its finances, is sent to the Council by the Central Government, then, the Council may, wherever`
  line `appropriate cause a special audit or take such other action as it considers necessary and shall furnish an`
  line `action taken report thereon to the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `^2[(5A) As soon as may be practicable at the end of each year, the Council shall circulate the audited accounts to its members at least fifteen days in advance and consider and approve these accounts in a special meeting convened for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(5B) The Council shall cause to be published in the Gazette of India not later than the 30th day of September of the year next following, a copy of the audited accounts and the Report of the Council for that year duly approved by the Council and copies of the said accounts and Report shall be forwarded to the Central Government and to all the members of the Institute.]`
  line
  line `(6) The Council may borrow from a scheduled bank as defined in the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), or from the Central Government--`
  line
  line `(a) any money required for meeting its liabilities on capital account on the security of the fund or on the security of any other assets for the time being belonging to it; or`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of meeting current liabilities pending the receipt of income by way of temporary loan or overdraft.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for sub-sections (3), (4) and (5) (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 52, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (744)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Register of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=744&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)The Council shall maintain a Register of members of the Institute in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed].`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[Register of members] shall include the following particulars about every member of the Institute, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) his full name, date of birth, domicile, residential and professional addresses;`
  line
  line `(b) the date on which his name is entered in the ^2[Register of members];`
  line
  line `(c) his qualifications;`
  line
  line `^3[(ca) whether any actionable information or complaint is pending or any penalty has been`
  line `imposed against him under Chapter V, including details thereof, if any;]`
  line
  line `(d) whether he holds a certificate of practice; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other particulars which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall cause to be published in such manner as may be prescribed a list of members of the Institute as on the 1st day of April of each year, and shall, if requested to do so by any such member, send him a copy of such list ^4[on payment of such amount as may be prescribed].`
  line
  line `^5[(4) Every member of the Institute shall, on his name being entered in the ^2[Register of members], pay such annual membership fee as may be determined, by notification, by the Council ^6***:`
  line
  line ^7*****.]
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 53, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 53, for “Register” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 17 (w.e.f. 17-11-20006).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `6. The words “, which shall not exceed rupees five thousand” omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 53 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `7. The proviso omitted by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (745)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Removal from the Register of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=745&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may remove from the ^1[Register of members] the name of any member of the Institute,--`
  line
  line `(a) who is dead; or`
  line
  line `(b) from whom a request has been received to that effect; or`
  line
  line `(c) who has not paid any prescribed fee required to be paid by him; or`
  line
  line `(d) who is found to have been subject at the time when his name was entered in the ^1[Register of members], or who at any time thereafter has become subject, to any of the disabilities mentioned in section 8, or who for any other reason has ceased to be entitled to have his name borne on the Register.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall remove from the ^1[Register of members] the name of any member in respect of whom an order has been passed under this Act removing him from membership of the Institute.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) If the name of any member has been removed from the Register under clause (c) of sub-section (1), on receipt of an application, his name may be entered again in the Register on payment of the arrears of annual fee and entrance fee along with such additional fee, as may be determined, by notification, by the Council ^3****:`
  line
  line ^4*****.]
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 54, ibid., for “Register” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 18 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `3.The words “which shall not exceed rupees two thousand” omitted by Act 12 of 2022, s. 54 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4.The proviso omitted by s. 54, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (746)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Disciplinary Directorate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for section 21 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=746&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Disciplinary Directorate.--(1) The Council shall, by notification, establish a Disciplinary Directorate headed by an officer of the Institute designated as Director (Discipline) and such other employees for making investigations in respect of any information or complaint received by it.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of any information or complaint along with the prescribed fee, the Director (Discipline) shall arrive at a prima facie opinion on the occurrence of the alleged misconduct.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Director (Discipline) is of the opinion that a member is guilty of any professional or other misconduct mentioned in the First Schedule, he shall place the matter before the Board of Discipline and where the Director (Discipline) is of the opinion that a member is guilty of any professional or other misconduct mentioned in the Second Schedule or in both the Schedules, he shall place the matter before the Disciplinary Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) In order to make investigations under the provisions of this Act, the Disciplinary Directorate shall follow such procedure as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a complainant withdraws the complaint, the Director (Discipline) shall place such withdrawal before the Board of Discipline or as the case may be, the Disciplinary Committee, and the said Board of Committee may, if it is of the view that the circumstances so warrant, permit the withdrawal at any stage.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (747)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 26
  title `Board of Discipline.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=747&sectionno=21A&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Board of Discipline.--(1) The Council shall constitute a Board of Discipline consisting of --`
  line
  line `(a) a person with experience in law and having knowledge of disciplinary matters and the`
  line `profession, to be its presiding officer;`
  line
  line `(b) two members one of whom shall be a member of the Council elected by the Council and the other member shall be the person designated under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(c) the Director (Discipline) shall function as the Secretary of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of Discipline shall follow summary disposal procedure in dealing with all the cases before it.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Board of Discipline is of the opinion that a member is guilty of a professional or other misconduct mentioned in the First Schedule, it shall afford to the member an opportunity of being heard before making any order against him and may thereafter take any one or more of the following actions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) reprimand the member;`
  line
  line `(b) remove the name of the member from the Register up to a period of three months;`
  line
  line `(c) impose such fine as it may think fit which may extend to rupees one lakh.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director (Discipline) shall submit before the Board of Discipline all information and`
  line `complaints where he is of the opinion that there is no prima facie case and the Board of Discipline may, if`
  line `it agrees with the opinion of the Director (Discipline), close the matter or in case of disagreement, may advise the Director (Discipline) to further investigate the matter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_b:
  sectionId (748)
  sectionNo 21B
  orderNo 27
  title `Disciplinary Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=748&sectionno=21B&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[21B. Disciplinary Committee.--(1) The Council shall constitute a Disciplinary Committee consisting of the President or the Vice-President of the Council as the Presiding Officer and two members to be elected from amongst the members of the Council and two members to be nominated by the Central`
  line `Government from amongst the persons of eminence having experience in the field of law, economics, business, finance or accountancy:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council may constitute more Disciplinary Committees as and when it considers necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The Disciplinary Committee while considering the cases placed before it, shall follow such procedure as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Disciplinary Committee is of the opinion that a member is guilty of a professional or other misconduct mentioned in the Second Schedule or both the First Schedule and the Second Schedule,it shall afford to the member an opportunity of being heard before making any order against him and may thereafter take any one or more of the following actions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) reprimand the member;`
  line
  line `(b) remove the name of the member from the Register permanently or for such period, as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(c) impose such fine as it may think fit, which may extend to rupees five lakhs.`
  line
  line `(4) The allowances payable to the members nominated by the Central Government shall be such as may be specified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_c:
  sectionId (749)
  sectionNo 21C
  orderNo 28
  title `Authority, Disciplinary Committee, Board of Discipline and Director (Discipline) to have powers of civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=749&sectionno=21C&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_21_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[21C. Authority, Disciplinary Committee, Board of Discipline and Director (Discipline) to have`
  line `powers of civil court.--For the purposes of an inquiry under the provisions of this Act, the Authority, the Disciplinary Committee, Board of Discipline and the Director (Discipline) shall have the same powers`
  line `as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document; and`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sections 21, 21A, 21B, 21C and 22, "member of the Institute" includes a person who was a member of the Institute on the date of the alleged misconduct although he has ceased to be a member of the Institute at the time of the inquiry.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_d:
  sectionId (750)
  sectionNo 21D
  orderNo 29
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=750&sectionno=21D&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_21_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[21D.Transitional provisions.--All complaints pending before the Council or any inquiry initiated by the Disciplinary Committee or any reference or appeal made to a High Court prior to the commencement of the Cost and Works Accountants (Amendment) Act, 2006 shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this Act, as if this Act had not been amended by the Cost and Works`
  line `Accountants (Amendment) Act, 2006.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (751)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 30
  title `Professional or other misconduct defined.`
  content `^1[22. Professional or other misconduct defined.-- For the purposes of this Act, the expression "professional or other misconduct" shall be deemed to include any act or omission provided in any of the Schedules but nothing in this section shall be construed to limit or abridge in any way the power conferred or duty cast on the Director (Discipline) under sub-section (1) of section 21 to inquire into the conduct of any member of the Institute under any other circumstances.]`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 21, for section 22 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=751&sectionno=22&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (752)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 31
  title `Constitution of Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=752&sectionno=22A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[22A. Constitution of Appellate Authority.--The Appellate Authority constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 22A of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949), shall be deemed to`
  line `be the Appellate Authority for the purposes of this Act subject to the modification that for clause (b) of`
  line `said sub-section (1), the following clause had been substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(b) the Central Government shall, by notification appoint two part-time members from amongst`
  line `the persons who have been members of the Council of the ^2[Institute of Cost Accountants of India]`
  line `for at least one full term and who is not a sitting member of the Council;".]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 22 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2012, s. 5, for "Institute of Cost and Works Accountants of India" (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_b:
  sectionId (753)
  sectionNo 22B
  orderNo 32
  title `Term of office of members of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 22 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=753&sectionno=22B&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[22B. Term of office of members of Authority.--A person appointed as a member shall hold office`
  line `for a term of three years from the date on which he enters upon his office or until he attains the age of`
  line `sixty-two years, whichever is earlier.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_c:
  sectionId (754)
  sectionNo 22C
  orderNo 33
  title `Procedure, etc., of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 22 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=754&sectionno=22C&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[22C. Procedure, etc., of Authority.--The provisions of section 22C, section 22D and section 22F of`
  line `the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) shall apply to the Authority in relation to allowances`
  line `and terms and conditions of service of its Chairperson and members and in the discharge of its functions`
  line `under this Act as they apply to it in the discharge of its functions under the Chartered Accountants Act,`
  line 1949.]
obj_root_law_sections_22_d:
  sectionId (755)
  sectionNo 22D
  orderNo 34
  title `Officers and other staff of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 22 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=755&sectionno=22D&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[22D. Officers and other staff of Authority.--(1) The Council shall make available to the Authority`
  line `such officers and other staff members as may be necessary for the efficient performance of the functions`
  line `of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances and conditions of service of the officers and other staff members of`
  line `the Authority shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_e:
  sectionId (756)
  sectionNo 22E
  orderNo 35
  title `Appeal to Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 22 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=756&sectionno=22E&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_22_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[22E. Appeal to Authority.--(1) Any member of the Institute aggrieved by any order of the Board of`
  line `Discipline or the Disciplinary Committee imposing on him any of the penalties referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 21A and sub-section (3) of section 21B, may within ninety days from the date`
  line `on which the order is communicated to him, prefer an appeal to the Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Director (Discipline) may also appeal against the decision of the Board of`
  line `Discipline or the Disciplinary Committee to the Authority if so authorised by the Council, within ninety`
  line `days:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Authority may entertain any such appeal after the expiry of the said period`
  line `of ninety days, if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may, after calling for the records of any case, revise any order made by the Board`
  line `of Discipline or the Disciplinary Committee under sub-section (3) of section 21A and sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 21B and may--`
  line
  line `(a) confirm, modify or set aside the order;`
  line
  line `(b) impose any penalty or set aside, reduce, or enhance the penalty imposed by the order;`
  line
  line `(c) remit the case to the Board of Discipline or Disciplinary Committee for such further enquiry`
  line `as the Authority considers proper in the circumstances of the case; or`
  line
  line `(d) pass such other order as the Authority thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall give an opportunity of being heard to the parties concerned before`
  line `passing any order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (757)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 36
  title `Constitution and functions of Regional Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=757&sectionno=23&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of advising and`
  line `assisting it on matters concerning its functions, the Council may constitute such Regional Councils as and when it deems fit for one or more of the regional constituencies that may be specified by the Central Government under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 9.`
  line
  line `(2) The Regional Councils shall be constituted in such manner and exercise such functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (758)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 37
  title `Penalty for falsely claiming to be a member, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=758&sectionno=24&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(i) not being a member of the Institute--`
  line
  line `(a) represents that he is a member of the Institute; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses the designation cost accountant; or`
  line
  line `(ii) being a member of the Institute, but not having a certificate of practice, represents that he is in`
  line `practice or practices as a cost accountant;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable on first conviction with fine which may extend to ^1[one lakh rupees], and on any`
  line `subsequent conviction with imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ^2[five lakh rupees], or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 63, for “one thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 63, ibid., for “five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (759)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 38
  title `Penalty for using name of the Council, awarding degrees of cost accountancy, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=759&sectionno=25&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save`
  line `as otherwise provided in this Act, no person shall,--`
  line
  line `(i) use a name or a common seal which is identical with the name or the common seal of the`
  line `Institute or so nearly resembles it as to deceive or as is likely to deceive the public;`
  line
  line `(ii) award any degree, diploma or certificate or bestow any designation which indicates or`
  line `purports to indicate the position or attainment of any qualification or competence in cost accountancy`
  line `similar to that of a member of the Institute; or`
  line
  line `(iii) seek to regulate in any manner whatsoever the profession of ^1[cost accountants].`
  line
  line `(2) Any person contravening the provisions of sub-section (1) shall, without prejudice to any other`
  line `proceedings which may be taken against him, ^2[be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six`
  line `months or with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees`
  line `or with both on first conviction], and on any subsequent conviction with imprisonment which may extend`
  line `to ^3[one year, or with fine which shall not be less than two lakh rupees but which may extend to ten lakh`
  line `rupees], or with both.`
  line
  line ^4*****
  line
  line `(4) If the Central Government is satisfied that any diploma or certificate or any designation granted or`
  line `conferred by any person other than the Institute, which purports to be a qualification in cost accountancy`
  line `but which, in the opinion of the Central Government, falls short of the standard of qualifications`
  line `prescribed for cost accountants and does not in fact indicate or purport to indicate the position or`
  line `attainment of any qualification or competence in cost accountancy similar to that of a member of the`
  line `Institute, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette and subject to such conditions as it may think fit to`
  line `impose, declare that this section shall not apply to such diploma or certificate or designation`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2012, s. 6, for cost and works accountants (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 64, for “be punishable on first conviction with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees”`
  line `(w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 64, ibid., for “six months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 7 of 2006, s. 23 (w.e.f. 8-8-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (760)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 39
  title `Companies not to engage in cost accountancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=760&sectionno=26&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No company, whether incorporated in`
  line `India or elsewhere, shall practice as cost accountants.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the "company" shall include any`
  line `limited liability partnership which has company as its partner for the purposes of this section.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) If any company contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), then every director, manager,`
  line `Secretary and any other officer who is knowingly a party to such contravention shall be punished on first`
  line `conviction with fine which shall not be less than two lakh rupees but which may extend to ten lakh`
  line `rupees, and on any subsequent conviction, with fine which shall not be less than four lakh rupees but`
  line `which may extend to twenty lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2012, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 65, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (761)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 40
  title `Unqualified persons not to sign documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=761&sectionno=27&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person other than a member of the`
  line `Institute shall sign any document on behalf of cost accountant in practice or a firm of such cost`
  line `accountants in his or its professional capacity.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall, without prejudice to any`
  line `other proceedings which may be taken against him, be punishable on first conviction with a fine not less`
  line `than ^2[one lakh rupees] but which may extend to ^3[five lakh rupees], and in the event of a second or`
  line `subsequent conviction with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with a fine not less`
  line `than ^4[two lakh rupees] but which may extend to ^5[ten lakh rupees[ or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 24, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 17-11-2006)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 66, for “five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “ one lakh rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “ten thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “ two lakh rupees” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (762)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 41
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=762&sectionno=28&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Act is a company,`
  line `the company as well as every person in charge of, and responsible to, the company for the conduct of its`
  line `business at the time of the commission of the offence shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall`
  line `be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or that the commission of the offence is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any`
  line `director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" with respect to any offence under section 24, section 25 or section 27, means any`
  line `body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals; and with respect to an offence`
  line `under section 26 means a body corporate; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (763)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 42
  title `Sanction to prosecute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=763&sectionno=29&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be prosecuted under this Act except on a complaint`
  line `made by or under the order of the Council or of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29_a:
  sectionId (764)
  sectionNo 29A
  orderNo 43
  title `Establishment of Quality Review Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=764&sectionno=29A&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[29A. Establishment of Quality Review Board.--(1) The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `constitute a Quality Review Board consisting of a Chairperson and four other members.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and members of the Board shall be appointed from amongst the persons of`
  line `eminence having experience in the field of law, economics, business, finance or accountancy.`
  line
  line `(3) Two members of the Board shall be nominated by the Council and other two members shall be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_b:
  sectionId (765)
  sectionNo 29B
  orderNo 44
  title `Functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=765&sectionno=29B&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[29B. Functions of Board.--The Board shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to make recommendations to the Council with regard to the quality of services provided by`
  line `the members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) to review the quality of services provided by the members of the Institute including cost audit`
  line `services; and`
  line
  line `(c) to guide the members of the Institute to improve the quality of services and adherence to the`
  line `various statutory and other regulatory requirements.]`
  line
  line `^2[(d) to forward cases of non-compliance with various statutory and regulatory requirements by`
  line `the members of the Institute or firms noticed by it during the course of its review, to the Disciplinary`
  line `Directorate for its examination.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 67 (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_c:
  sectionId (766)
  sectionNo 29C
  orderNo 45
  title `Procedure of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=766&sectionno=29C&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_29_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[29C. Procedure of Board.--The Board shall meet at such time and place and follow in its meetings`
  line `such procedure as may be specified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_d:
  sectionId (767)
  sectionNo 29D
  orderNo 46
  title `Terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and members of Board and its expenditure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=767&sectionno=29D&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_29_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[29D. Terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and members of Board and its`
  line `expenditure.--(1) The terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and the members of the Board,`
  line `and their allowances shall be such as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenditure of the Board shall be borne by the Council.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (768)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 47
  title `Dissolution of the Institute of Cost and Works Accountants registered under the Companies Act, 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=768&sectionno=30&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `On the commencement of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the company known as the Institute of Cost and Works Accountants registered under the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall be dissolved and thereafter no person shall make, assert or`
  line `take any claims, demands or proceedings against the dissolved company or against any officer thereof`
  line `in his capacity as such officer except in so far as may be necessary, for enforcing the provisions of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the right of every member to or in respect of the dissolved company shall be extinguished, and`
  line `thereafter no member of that company shall make, assert or take any claims or demands or`
  line `proceedings in respect of that company except as provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (769)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 48
  title `Transfer of assets and liabilities of the dissolved company to the Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=769&sectionno=31&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the`
  line `commencement of this Act, there shall be transferred to and vested in the Institute all the assets and`
  line `liabilities of the dissolved company.`
  line
  line `(2) The assets of the dissolved company shall be deemed to include all rights and powers, and all`
  line `property, whether movable or immovable of the company, including, in particular, cash balances, reserve`
  line `funds, investments, deposits and all other interests and rights in or arising out of such property as may be`
  line `in the possession of the dissolved company and all books of accounts or documents of the dissolved`
  line `company; and the liabilities shall be deemed to include all debts, liabilities and obligations of whatever`
  line `kind then existing of that company.`
  line
  line `(3) All contracts, debts, bonds, agreements and other instruments of whatever nature to which the`
  line `dissolved company is a party, subsisting or having effect immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act, shall be of as full force and effect against or in favour of the Institute, as the case may be, and may be`
  line `enforced as fully and effectively as if instead of the dissolved company, the Institute had been a party`
  line thereto.
  line
  line `(4) If, on the commencement of this Act, any suit, appeal or other legal proceeding of whatever nature`
  line `by or against the dissolved company is pending, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be in any`
  line `way prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer to the Institute of the assets and liabilities of the`
  line `dissolved company or of anything contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be`
  line `continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the Institute, in the same manner and to the same extent`
  line `as it would or may be continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the dissolved company if this Act`
  line `had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (770)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 49
  title `Provisions respecting employees of the dissolved company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=770&sectionno=32&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person employed in the`
  line `dissolved company prior to the 1st day of September, 1958 , and still in its employment immediately`
  line `before the commencement of this Act shall, as from such commencement, become an employee of the`
  line `Institute, shall hold his office or service therein by the same tenure and upon the same terms and`
  line `conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to pension and gratuity as he would have held the`
  line `same under the dissolved company if this Act had not been passed, and shall continue to do so unless and`
  line `until his employment in the Institute is terminated or until his remuneration, terms and conditions of`
  line `employment are duly altered by the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force the transfer of the services of any employee of the dissolved`
  line `company to the Institute shall not entitle any such employee to any compensation under that Act or other`
  line `law, and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (771)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 50
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=771&sectionno=33&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `[Appeals.] Omitted by Cost and Works (Amendment) Act, 2006 (7 of 2006), s. 26`
  line `(w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (49062)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 51
  title `Alteration in the Register and cancellation of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=49062&sectionno=34&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an order is made under`
  line `this Act reprimanding a member a record of the punishment shall be entered against his name in the`
  line Register.
  line
  line `(2) Where the name of any member is removed, the certificate of practice granted to him under this`
  line `Act shall be recalled and cancelled.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (49063)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 52
  title `Directions of the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=49063&sectionno=35&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may from time to time`
  line `issue such directions to the Council as in the opinion of the Central Government are conducive to the`
  line `fulfilment of the objects of this Act and in the discharge of its functions, the Council shall be bound to`
  line `carry out any such directions.`
  line
  line `(2) Directions issued under sub-section (1) may include directions to the Council to make any`
  line `regulations or to amend or revoke any regulations already made.`
  line
  line `(3) If, in the opinion of the Central Government the Council has persistently made default in giving`
  line `effect to the directions issued under this section, the Central Government may, after giving an opportunity`
  line `to the Council to state its case, by order, dissolve the Council, where after a new Council shall be`
  line `constituted in accordance with the provisions of this Act with effect from such date as may be specified`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Central Government passes an order under sub-section (3) dissolving the Council, it`
  line `may, pending the constitution of a new Council in accordance with the provisions of this Act, authorise`
  line `any person or body of persons to take over the management of the affairs of the Institute and to exercise`
  line `such functions as may be specified in this behalf by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (49064)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 53
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 27, for section 36 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=49064&sectionno=36&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[36. Protection of action taken in good faith.--No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or the Council or the Authority or the Disciplinary Committee or the`
  line `Tribunal or the Board or the Board of Discipline or the Disciplinary Directorate or any officer of that`
  line `Government, Council, Authority, Disciplinary Committee, Tribunal, Board, Board of Discipline or the`
  line `Disciplinary Directorate, for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or`
  line `any rule, regulation, notification, direction or order made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_a:
  sectionId (49065)
  sectionNo 36A
  orderNo 54
  title `Members, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=49065&sectionno=36A&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[36A. Members, etc., to be public servants.--The Chairperson, Presiding Officer, members and`
  line `other officers and employees of the Authority, Disciplinary Committee, Tribunal, Board, Board of`
  line `Discipline or the Disciplinary Directorate shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (49066)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 55
  title `Maintenance of branch offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=49066&sectionno=37&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a cost accountant in practice or a firm of such cost`
  line `accountants has more than one office in India, each one of such offices shall be in the separate charge of a`
  line `member of the Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council may in suitable cases exempt any cost accountant in practice or firm of`
  line `such cost accountants from the operation of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) Every cost accountant in practice or firm of such cost accountants maintaining more than one`
  line `office shall send to the Council a list of offices and the persons in charge thereof and shall keep the`
  line `Council informed of any changes in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (49067)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 56
  title Reciprocity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 69, for “Register” (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=49067&sectionno=38&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any country, specified by the Central Government in this behalf by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, prevents persons of Indian domicile from becoming members of any`
  line `institution similar to the Institute established under this Act or from practicing the profession of costs accountancy or subject them to unfair discrimination in that country, no subject of any such country shall be entitled to become a member of the Institute or practice the profession of cost accountancy, in India.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Council may prescribe the conditions, if any, subject to which foreign qualifications relating to cost accountancy shall be recognised for the purposes of entry in the ^1Register of members].`
obj_root_law_sections_38_a:
  sectionId (49068)
  sectionNo 38A
  orderNo 57
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=49068&sectionno=38A&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Power of Central Government to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of election and nomination in respect of members to the Council under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of service of the Presiding Officer and Members of the Tribunal,`
  line `place of meetings and allowances to be paid to them under sub-section (5) of section 10B;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) the form and fee for filing an information or a complaint under sub-section (1), the manner`
  line `of deciding a complaint or information as actionable or non-actionable under sub-section (2) and the`
  line `procedure of investigation under sub-section (7), of section 21;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure while considering the cases by the Board of Discipline under sub-section (2) and time limit for payment of fine under sub-section (7), of section 21A;`
  line
  line `(da) the procedure while considering the cases by the Disciplinary Committee under`
  line `sub-section (2) and time limit for payment of fine under sub-section (7), of section 21B;]`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure to be followed by the Board in its meetings under section 29C; and`
  line
  line `(f) the terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and members of the Board under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 29D.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2006, s. 29 (w.e.f. 17-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2022, s. 70, for clauses (c) and (d) (w.e.f. 10-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (49069)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587&sectionId=49069&sectionno=39&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00003_195923_1517807321587
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, by notification in the Gazette of India,`
  line `make regulations for the purpose of carrying out the objects of this Act, ^1***.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the standard and conduct of examinations under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the qualifications for the entry of the name of any person in the ^2[Register of members] as a member of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(c) the qualification required for the purposes of sub-section (4) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions under which any examination or training may be treated as equivalent to the`
  line `examination or training prescribed for members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions under which any foreign qualification may be recognised;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which applications for entry in the 2^[Register of members] may be made;`
  line
  line `(g) the fees payable for membership of the Institute and the annual fees payable by associates and`
  line `fellows of the Institute in respect of their certificates;`
  line
  line 3^****;
  line
  line `(i) the particulars to be entered in the Register;`
  line
  line 4^****;
  line
  line `(k) the regulation and maintenance of the status and standard of professional qualifications of`
  line `members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(l) the carrying out of research in accountancy;`
  line
  line `(m) the maintenance of libraries and publication of books and periodicals relating to cost accountancy and allied subjects;`
  line
  line `(n) the management of the property of the Council and the maintenance and audit of its accounts;`
  line
  line `(o) the summoning and holding of meetings of the Council and committees thereof, the times and places of such meetings, the procedure to be followed thereat and the number of members necessary to form a quorum;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner in which the annual list of 5^[members of] the Institute shall be published;`
  line
  line `(q) the powers, duties and functions of the President and the Vice-President of the Council;`
  line
  line `(r) the functions of the Standing and other committees and the conditions subject to which such functions shall be discharged;`
  line
  line `6^(s) the circumstances under which certificates of practice may be cancelled under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(sa) the guidelines for granting or refusal of certificates of practice under clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(sb) the manner of appointment, powers, duties, functions, salaries, fees, allowances and other`
  line `terms and conditions of service of the Secretary and other officers and employees of the Council`
  line `under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(sc) the manner of preparing annual financial statement under sub-section (4) and the annual`
  line `accounts under sub-section (5), of section 18;`
  line
  line `(sd) the manner of maintaining a Register of the members of the Institute under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 19;`
  line
  line `(se) the manner of making an application for grant of registration of a firm and the terms and`
  line `conditions of such registration under section 20A;`
  line
  line `(sf) the manner of maintenance of Register of firms and other particulars including details of`
  line `pendency of any actionable information or complaint or imposition of any penalty against the firm`
  line `under sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) and the manner in which the annual list of firms registered`
  line `with the Institute shall be published under sub-section (3), of section 20B;`
  line
  line `(sg) the manner of making available status of actionable information and complaints and orders`
  line `passed under sub-section (9) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(sh) the manner of preparing panel of persons under clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (1) and`
  line `the allowances payable to the Presiding Officers and members of Board of Discipline under`
  line `sub-section (8), of section 21A;`
  line
  line `(si) the manner of preparing panel of persons under clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (1) and`
  line `the allowances payable to the Presiding Officers and members of the Disciplinary Committees under`
  line `sub-section (8), of section 21B;`
  line
  line `(sj) the salaries and allowances and conditions of service of officers and other staff of the`
  line `Authority under sub-section (2) of section 22D;`
  line
  line `(sk) the manner in which Regional Council may be constituted under sub-section (2) of section 23`
  line `and the functions thereof;`
  line
  line `7^* * * * *`
  line
  line `(u) the terms and conditions of service of persons who have become employees of the Institute under section 32 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) the registration and training of students and the fees to be charged therefor; and`
  line
  line `(w) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) All regulations made by the Council under this Act shall be subject to the condition of previous publication and to the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the Central Government may frame the first regulations for the purposes mentioned in this section, and such regulations shall be deemed to have been made by the Council, and shall remain in force until they are amended, altered or revoked by the Council.`
  line
  line 8^*****
